rComments: He really wanted you to succeed and did his best to make his course interesting. He is very nice and reasonable with grading and will give good feedback. Obviously don't slack, but if you put in a normal amount of work then it is rewarding. You also get points for participation which is nice. Very nice guy, added me on Overwatch lol

If you take this class, I strongly recommend that you take Professor Chipman. He cares a lot about his students' success and is more than happy to answer questions and set up office hours. He is also very prompt in answering his emails. No exams, just short essays and a group final presentation - pretty easy class.

When I took APA I don't know anything about it until I took this course as an elective. Learning from Phillip was great no midterms, no quiz, no exams nothing just three short assignments and If you have any problems with the assignments he can help and understand clearly. Also final project with group. Overall, he's great I recommend him.

Fantastic professor! He made lecture content that I didn't find particularly interesting so engaging! He is very clear about expectations and is helpful both in and outside of class. I would say that though attendance is not mandatory you get so much more from his class if you do attend. All in all my best prof yet!
Okay subject, but this prof is able to make it interesting Hes funny, caring and passionate about the content which helps a lot! Would definitely take professor Chipman again!

I took this class as an APA elective and I do not regret it. No midterms, only 3 short assignments and a final group presentation. Attend class, you won't regret it. He is a very fair grader so long as you put in the effort. He looks for improvement and I loved that about him. I hope to have this prof again!

Where to start... Professor Chipman is by far the best prof I've ever had. He makes every lesson super interesting and tries to make it interactive too. He answers his emails super quickly and truly makes you feel at ease. He also cares about your mental health and always reminds us to take it easy. Respected man for sure!
